Final Project: Part One

You will develop some sort of artificial intelligence program.  What you build and how you go about it is up to you; you just need some kind of artificial intelligence program that has a specific use case to work with.  You can build any sort of artificial intelligence as long as it serves a specific purpose.

The best way to think about this in relation to your annotated bibliography and other research components is that this is the experiment of your ethical research.  This is the practice put into place of the ideas you have been working with the entire course.  You have the structural understanding of decency and the ethical framework in place so using your technical skill, you can put it into practice.
Final Project: Part Two

Over this course, we have looked at how to construct an ethical framework while also looking at specific frameworks and ideologies.  The main focus has been on the aspect of decency. You must take your constructed AI and explain how it is ethical.  To do this, you must provide a video demonstration and explanation of your artificial intelligence and how it should be considered ethical. 

    Your video should include a demo of your program while also laying out the ethical framework you are using. 
        What steps did you take in the development to ensure its ethical use? 
        How would this AI be implemented to insure it is being used properly, ethically, and justly?  

Your presentation should 10 - 15 minutes with demonstration of your program included.  Submit your video presentation and all accompanying files needed to support it. 